social_posts.post_text: One of the most beautiful distilleries we visited on the Bourbon Trail was @castleandkey. A must see if you pass through the area.

Yesterday’s instameet was so much fun. I’m passionate about plants and got to spend a few hot and sweaty hours with them and learned so much thanks to @plantsalive and @cultivatethecity. Highly recommend a drive out to see how fabulous the place is for yourself. #igdc

Visited @burnsidefarms for the first time yesterday. This is the same place you see the amazing tulip photos from every spring and their sunflower fields did not disappoint. We went late for fireworks so the sun hit directly behind the blooms. It can be a challenge to photograph but I tried to lean into the brightness. 

Tonight I’m headed to McKee-Beshers with @igdc for our annual sunflower trek. Hope to see you there! #igdc 🌻

Today @bigntoasty, @beingdave and I drove out to Leesburg, VA in search of rainbows. We found kindness and were not disappointed. 

Homeowner Margie Hunter and her daughter started the Kindness Rock Garden 3 years ago and every single item is made by her and her daughter, including the Little Free Library (complete with lights and a fairy door). Their guiding star: “the right message at the right moment can change someone’s whole day—and maybe even change a life.” Every small detail is carefully thought through and executed, including small handmade gifts of reassurance and kindness that visitors can take with them. Leave a wish on the wishing tree and don’t, for one second think her husband had anything to do with the garden. 

We were moved by their work and the dedication, generosity, craftsmanship and humor truly made this a memorable weekend adventure. #igdc

Little Amal has journeyed over 6,000 miles in 15 countries and is currently walking another 6,000 across the United States. Amal is a 12 foot puppet of a 10 year old Syrian refugee and has become a symbol of human rights. Through her walks she raises awareness and reminds us to not forget about refugees and people in need. #walkwithamal #igdc

Thank you to the @hirshhorn for the preview yesterday of ‘Simone Leigh’. The exhibition is the first museum survey of the acclaimed artist in Washington, DC. @simoneyvetteleigh, who was on-hand to walk us through the exhibition, discussed how she creates works of art that focus on Black female subjectivity and employs materials and forms traditionally associated with African art. The works are monumental and powerful and when the show opens on Nov. 3rd, I highly recommend you not miss it. #igdc

Magic, Wonder, and Joy at the White House. Candy, trains, whimsy and traditions merged in a stunning display that celebrated the 200th anniversary of the publication of ‘Twas the Night Before Christmas. #igdc

Yesterday @wreathsacross mobilized across the country to lay wreaths at the graves of service men and women across the country. It was my first time participating at @arlingtonnatl and it was truly an amazing experience. Thousands of volunteers help put wreaths on approx 400,000 graves over a few hours. To watch the cemetery fill up so fast and to hear the singing of truck drivers as they distribute wreaths are memories I’ll keep with me. #igdc
